
# skel-startmenu reads a directory, and creates 
# a menu based on the filenames in the directory. 
# those files are typically simple program wrapper 
# scripts to start one or more X applications 
# with a little bit of intelligence.  

# START WRAPPERS

# automenu should become autoexec and take a path 
# list, rather than use a default. This will give 
# one program the ability to provide multiple 
# policies.  

### AUTOGENERATED MENUS

PipeRead '$[XTOOLPATH]/fvwm-execmenu -m OfficeMenu -p $[XSTARTPATH]'

PipeRead '$[XTOOLPATH]/fvwm-execmenu -m GraphicsMenu -p $[XSTARTPATH]'
PipeRead '$[XTOOLPATH]/fvwm-execmenu -m AudioMenu -p $[XSTARTPATH]'
PipeRead '$[XTOOLPATH]/fvwm-execmenu -m ProjectMenu -p $[XSTARTPATH]'
PipeRead '$[XTOOLPATH]/fvwm-execmenu -m FiveOn -p $[XMACROPATH]'

### SUB MAIN MENUS 

# WINDOW MANAGER MENU
DestroyMenu MacroMenu
AddToMenu MacroMenu
+ "F-&Key" exec $[XTOOLPATH]/fvwm-fkeybind
+ "Terminals &5" Popup FiveOn
+ "RunTail &Cll" $[XMACROPATH]/RunTail.cll.sh 

# PRE MAIN MENU SHIM 
DestroyFunc Run_LeftMenu
AddToFunc Run_LeftMenu
+ I Refresh_LeftMenu 
+ I Menu LeftClickMenu

### MAIN MENU

DestroyFunc Refresh_LeftMenu
AddToFunc Refresh_LeftMenu
+ I DestroyMenu LeftClickMenu
+ I AddToMenu LeftClickMenu
+ I + 'File&Manager'   	exec $[XSTARTPATH]/NoMenu.FileManager.sh
+ I + ""	Nop
+ I + "Office"		Popup  	OfficeMenu
+ I + "Code"		Popup  	CodeMenu
+ I + "Graphics"	Popup 	GraphicsMenu
+ I + "A&udio"		Popup   AudioMenu
+ I + ""	Nop
+ I AddToMenu LeftClickMenu 
+ I + "M&acros"	Popup   MacroMenu
+ I + "Project"	Popup   ProjectMenu
+ I + ""	Nop

